[src:1900-in-association-football/1850s-in-association-football] Included are events in closely related codes, such as the Sheffield Rules.
[src:1900-in-association-football/1860s-in-association-football] The following are events in the 1860s decade which are relevant to the development of association football.
[src:1900-in-association-football/1860s-in-association-football] There was constant discussion about the rules throughout this decade and several codes were in use.
[src:1900-in-association-football/1860s-in-association-football] The Football Association (the FA) was founded in 1863 and its rules eventually prevailed.
[src:1900-in-association-football/1860s-in-association-football] Points at issue among the various associations included offside, the throw-in, the corner kick, the crossbar and the now-obsolete touch down.
[src:1900-in-association-football/1860s-in-association-football] Among the clubs founded in the 1860s were Notts County, Nottingham Forest, Queen's Park FC, Sheffield Wednesday, Stoke City and Kilmarnock.
